    "body": "### Problem\n\nVersion impacted: 0.11.2\n\n### Issue\n\nCurrent setup: When i open folder using `nvim .` , and i uses nvim.persistance plugin that opens up last opened files. I also have lsp config setup.\n\nAfter the upgrade  0.11.1 -> 0.11.2 : I noticed that the first file in the buffer has lsp plugins inactive: no color highlight, no code completion.  Once i close the current buffer and open the file again, it appear. \n\n\n\n\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nSince i have lots of plugins setup: snacks.nvim and its entire ecosystem, it's difficult to pinpoint why this is happening.  This issue was never there with the old version of nvim\n\nLogs(`LspLog` also do not say much: just : `rust-analyzer doesn't have a configuration` < which isnt' an issue AFAIK\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nthe first file it open should have color highlight and lsp should work\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.11.2\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nI only use Nvim\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOs 15.5\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\niterm, wezterm\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nbrew install for latest, and  to fix the issue, i had to install 0.11.1 from tar file",
